profile_positions.description:
As non-elected member of D66 political group, I was tasked with advising the councillors of the D66 political group concerning the following policy areas: 
- Citizen participation and democratic renewal;
- Region & intermunicipal cooperation;
- Mobility. 

At the start of my membership, a unique situation in Dutch local public administration occurred. A merger took place between a coalition and opposition party, which changed the mutual relations in the municipal council. During this process, I contributed to the approach of the D66 political group and put forward political-administrative considerations.

As project coordinator at Necker my tasks and responsibilities consisted of:
- facilitating the research that is conducted by Necker;
- preparation and editing of documents and offers;
- overhauling the Necker website;
- carrying out all kinds of ad hoc matters;
- conducting surveys under colleagues with Survalyzer;
- project management.

As project assistant at Citisens my tasks and responsibilities consisted of:
- creating 183 voting advice applications as a team;
- researching the local political environment of each municipality;
- creating circa 35 statements per municipality;
- programming the voting advice applications;
- answering questions from local politicians or clerks by telephone or in writing;
- reviewing the positions of political parties.

As ''boekenfonds'' employee at Laar & Berg, my tasks and responsibilities consisted of:
- making an inventory of the books;
- paying attention to the condition of the books;
- ensuring that the supplies for the following school year have been purchased;
- preparing the books so the next school year can start easily.

volunteer_experiences.description:
As member of the European Union working group my tasks and responsibilities consist of:
- stimulating the political discussion on various topics regarding the European Union within the Young Democrats (Jonge Democraten);
- co-developing the political line of the Young Democrats (Jonge Democraten) concerning the European Union.

As research secretary of the Foreign Affairs working group my tasks and responsibilities consist of:
- setting up the research subgroup of the working group;
- facilitating the research that is conducted by working group members;
- discussing research proposals with working group members.

As member of the Foreign Affairs working group my tasks and responsibilities consist of:
- stimulating the political discussion on various topics concerning international affairs within the Young Democrats;
- organizing a Model United Nations with multiple political youth wing with various political philosophies;
- exploring options that the EU can utilize to prevent future conflicts.

As member of the International working group my tasks and responsibilities consist of:
- stimulating the political discussion on various topics concerning international affairs amongst D66 members;
- stimulating D66 members to keep up with developments in the international arena;
- co-developing the D66 vision on international affairs.

As member of the Europe working group my tasks and responsibilities consist of:
- stimulating the political discussion on various topics concerning the EU amongst D66 members;
- stimulating D66 members to keep up with developments in EU institutions;
- co-developing the D66 vision of the EU.

As member of the Working Group Policy Book Renewal my tasks and responsibilities consist of:
- evaluating, revising, and co-developing the political line of the European Liberal Youth concerning external relations and foreign affairs;
- revising resolutions concerning sustainability and democracy in Tunisie and the conflict on the Nagorno-Karabakh peace deal.

As Social Media Content Creator for D66 Gooise Meren my tasks and responsibilities consist of:
- creating content for the local chapter's Instagram and Facebook pages;
- coordinate content for the Instagram and Facebook pages, and the local chapter's website with the website administrator;
- co-managing the Instagram and Facebook pages of the local chapter.

As member of the evaluation committee for D66 Gooise Meren my tasks and responsibilities consist of:
- evaluating the effectiveness of the activities of the election committees, the board and the faction in the run-up to the municipal elections in 2022;
- consulting secondary sources to evaluate this process;
- interviewing those involved in this process;
- writing recommendations for improving the preparation of future municipal elections.

As Vice-chair of the Career Committee my tasks and responsibilities consisted of:
- chairing various meetings;
- acting as a replacement for the Chairman;
- the evaluation of all 5 organized activities;
- writing the transfer document;
- the acquisition of organizations.

As Treasurer of the Career Committee my tasks and responsibilities consisted of:
- preparing the Career Committee's budget for the academic year 2021-2022;
- managing the Career Committee's treasury.

As head of the Geopolitics Europe division at Varemeng my tasks and responsibilities consisted of:
- leading a team of 12 senior and junior writers
- stimulate them to develop and perfect their writing skills;
- approving topics for articles;
- proofreading and reviewing articles;
- maintaining professional and academic standards of writing.

As senior writer at Varemeng my tasks and responsibilities consisted of:
- writing analytical essays concerning geopolitics in Europe, and the economy;
- maintaining professional, and academic standards of writing.
